  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this paper we prove, as conjectured by B. Banachewski and C.J. Mulvey, that the constructive Gelfand duality can be extended into a duality between compact regular locales and unital abelian localic <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msup><mrow><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>⁎</mo></mrow></msup></math> -algebras. In order to do so we develop a constructive theory of localic metric spaces and localic Banach spaces, we study the notion of localic completion of such objects and the behavior of these constructions with respect to pull-back along geometric morphisms.</subfield>
